b'It\xe2\x80\x99s #WellnessWednesday, and we want to talk sleep :sleeping_face:. Your body needs sleep to help your immune system work properly. b':sparkles: Do you know the difference between cleaning and disinfecting? It all has to do with how you remove germs from a surface. *Cleaning physically removes dirt, germs and impurities from a surface. *Disinfecting uses chemicals to kill germs on a surface but doesn\xe2\x80\x99t necessarily remove the germs or dirt. Check out the link in our bio to shop and for more information on cleaning and disinfecting high-touch surfaces. #StayPreparedWithCVS'

b'It\xe2\x80\x99s #WellnessWednesday and we want to tell you more about vitamin C. This mighty vitamin may help the immune system as it works to protect the body from disease and helps make collagen, which helps support wounds healing.* Vitamin C isn\xe2\x80\x99t just found in citrus: tomatoes :tomato:, white potatoes :potato: and broccoli :broccoli: all have vitamin C. Your body doesn\xe2\x80\x99t make it naturally, so you need to get it from your diet or a supplement. Contact a health care professional before starting any supplementation. Check out our Instagram Stories to learn more! #StayPreparedwithCVS\n\n*Statement not evaluated by the Food and Drug Administration (FDA).'

b"Frantzcesca Casimir, Health and Wellness Coach, shares some ways that you can support your immune system to help prevent the flu.  Don't miss her go-to immunity support smoothie recipe and exercise tips! #TakeoverTuesdays"

b'We\xe2\x80\x99re all adjusting to a new routine, but does your new routine help support your immunity? Check out these simple things you can do every day to help support your wellness. :sweat_droplets: Stay hydrated. Dehydration can make you more susceptible to illness. :woman_running_selector: Exercise regularly. Exercise can improve your circulation, which can support wellness. :sleeping_face: Get quality sleep. Your body needs sleep to help support wellness. :person_in_lotus_position: Manage stress levels. Ongoing stress may have an impact on your immune system. :broccoli: Eat a healthy diet. Healthy diets can be important for helping support immune systems. :flexed_biceps: Get a flu shot. A flu shot can help keep you from getting sick and help protect others around you. Schedule your flu shot and shop link in bio to #StayPreparedWithCVS.'

b':sparkles: It\xe2\x80\x99s #WellnessWednesday! Today we\xe2\x80\x99re talking about flu shots and how they can help protect you from the flu. Flu shots can help keep you and those around you from getting the flu. Because the flu virus changes over time and your protection from the flu shot declines over time, getting a vaccine every year is recommended for the best protection. The Centers for Disease Control and Protection (CDC) recommends getting your flu shot by the end of October so your shot can help protect you throughout the flu season. \n\n:backhand_index_pointing_up:Check out our Instagram Stories and visit the link in bio to schedule your flu shot!'

b':face_savoring_food: Snack better with these fun-to-make energy bites that are kid friendly and full of wholesome ingredients.

What you\xe2\x80\x99ll need:
2 cups nuts
3/4 cup pitted dates
1/2 cup dried strawberries

The steps:
Use a food processor to chop the nuts.
Set the nuts aside.
Use a food processor to chop the fruit.
Mix all the ingredients together.
Form the mixture into small balls using your hands.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes to set.

Substitutes:
Don\xe2\x80\x99t have these ingredients? Try experimenting with nut butter, oats, dried fruit, and honey. No food processor required! Mix everything in a bowl, roll into bites, and chill for similar results.'
